## Round 10 addendum: every PR now passes the repo lint (type checkers included)
User asked to 'ensure all PRs pass linting'. The repo's CI lint gate
(nox -e lint -> prek pre-push hooks) effectively runs THREE always_run
type checkers repo-wide — ty, pyright@1.1.387 (relaxed: attr/call/arg
checks off, tests excluded), and mypy@1.19.1 (tests excluded, weave.*
has disallow_untyped_defs/calls) — while the ruff hooks only see staged
files. So 'passing lint' per PR means every intermediate module state
must type-check.

Found and fixed two classes of problems:
1. Stage-ordering forward references: _compile_expanded_field /
   _resolve_ref_str_for_filter / _expand_refs lived in the late
   refs-threads stage but were called from the compile/read stages —
   mypy attr-defined errors on 5 intermediate branches (the Protocol base
   covers PUBLIC methods, so only private helpers can dangle). Fixed by
   moving them to their first callers; _compile_calls_sort_field moved
   into the compilation stage to keep the read stage in size budget.
   New deltas: compile 573, read 595, eval-subtree+threads 179.
2. 16 genuine mypy errors in the canonical module (never caught before
   because an earlier scoped mypy run had silently executed against the
   skeleton branch — the gt-track HEAD footgun AGAIN): Optional
   started_at/ended_at flow from the part-merge change (latency, threads
   aggregation — restructured with explicit non-None narrowing),
   calls_delete re-binding a comprehension-typed name to an Optional,
   feedback_aggregate narrowing time_bucket_seconds and reusing 'key'
   for both a list and tuple, _log_completion_span response now
   dict | None (open stream spans), _ch_sorted_by_terms terms param
   widened to Sequence (invariance), _ch_position bool() coercion,
   _orm_select 'out' no-redef rename.

